Shows the life and culture of the Thao family, Hmong Americans in Appleton, Wisconsin. The film focuses on Paja Thao, a shaman whose spiritual leadership plays a vital role in Appleton's Hmong community. He ministers to the physical and spiritual needs of friends and family with elaborate rituals that bridge the natural and spirit worlds. However, as Paja's children have grown up, they are losing touch with their father's 5,000 year old traditions. Directed by Taggart Siegel. c2001. 58 min. ; 
